<http://www.oie.int/messages/060821bel.htm>

Bluetongue In Belgium
---------------------------
(Disease never reported before in Belgium).
Translation of information received on 19 Aug 2006 from Dr. Luc
Lengele, Chief Veterinary Officer, Federal State Service for Public
Health, Food Chain Safety and Environment, Sanitary Political Service
Animals and Plants, Brussels:
Report date: 19 Aug 2006.
Reason for immediate notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
or infection in a country.
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 18 Aug 2006.
Date of start of the event: 18 Aug 2006.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical and laboratory.
11 outbreaks of bluetongue have been reported in 17 bovine (7 farms)
and in 4 ovine (4 farms)
Bluetongue was confirmed on the basis of atypical clinical signs of
the disease.
Location of outbreaks: Liege and Limburg provinces.
Diagnostic tests used: ELISA and RT-PCR.
Further details will be published in the next issue of weekly Disease
Information, available on line from Thu 24 Aug 2006 afternoon (GMT).
--
OIE Animal Health Information Department
<information.dept@oie.int>
