Bluetongue In Germany
---------------------------
(Disease never reported before in Germany).
Information received on 21 Aug 2006 from Prof. Dr. Werner Zwingmann,
Chief Veterinary Officer, Ministry of Consumer Protection, Food and
Agriculture, Bonn:
Report date: 21 Aug 2006.
Reason for immediate notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
or infection in a country.
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 21 Aug 2006.
Date of start of the event: 21 Aug 2006.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical and laboratory.
Two outbreaks of bluetongue have been reported in North Rhine
Wesphalia: in ovine in Kreis Aachen (2 cases) and in bovine in Stadt
Aachen (15 cases).
Description of affected population:
Kreis Aachen
One holding with 17 breeding sheep aged over one year.
Stadt Aachen
One holding with 199 breeding cattle.
One holding with 64 breeding cattle.
One holding with 106 breeding cattle.
One holding with 264 breeding cattle.
One holding with 68 breeding cattle.
Laboratory where diagnostic tests were performed: Friedrich-Loeffler
Institute, Insel Riems (OIE Reference Laboratory).
Diagnostic tests used: cELISA.
Source of outbreaks or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive.
Control measures undertaken:
- movement control inside the country
- screening
- zoning
--
OIE Animal Health Information Department
<information.dept@oie.int>
